Constructor Detail

LaTeXReportGenerator

public LaTeXReportGenerator()
Constructs a new instance of LaTeX export. For each document to be translated a new instance has to be created. Here default values are used (A4 paper, 11pt, portrait, fancy headings, no titlepage).

LaTeXReportGenerator

public LaTeXReportGenerator(boolean landscape,
                            boolean typeWriter,
                            short fontSize,
                            String paperSize,
                            boolean addPredefinedUnits,
                            boolean titlepage,
                            boolean printNameIfAvailable)
Constructs a new instance of LaTeX export. For each document to be translated a new instance has to be created. This constructor allows you to set many properties of the resulting LaTeX file.

Parameters:
landscape - If true the whole document will be set to landscape format, otherwise portrait.
typeWriter - If true ids are set in typewriter font (default). Otherwise the regular font is used.
fontSize - The size of the font to be used here. The default is 11. Allowed values are 8, 9, 10, 11, 12, 14, 16 and 17.
paperSize - Allowed are
  • letter
  • legal
  • executive
  • a* where * stands for values from 0 thru 9
  • b*
  • c*
  • d*
addPredefinedUnits - If true predefined SBML units will be made explicitly if not overridden in the model.
titlepage - if true a title page will be created for the model report. Default is false (just a caption).

callsFunctions

public List<String> callsFunctions(org.sbml.jsbml.ASTNode ast)
For a given empty list of function identifiers this method performs DFS to detect all functions called by the expression hidden in the given ASTNode and returns the filled list of function identifiers. Every function called in this tree is added only one time to the list (in the order the functions are called).

Parameters:
ast -
funcIDs -
Returns:

isArrangeReactionParticipantsInOneTable

public boolean isArrangeReactionParticipantsInOneTable()
This switch allows to change the way how the reactants, modifiers and products are presented in each reaction. If true, one table is created containing the identifiers of each reactant, modifier and product together with the respective name. If false (default), a subsection for each one of the three groups of participants is created giving all details of each participant.

Returns:
The state of this switch.

setArrangeReactionParticipantsInOneTable

public void setArrangeReactionParticipantsInOneTable(boolean arrangeReactionParticipantsInOneTable)
This switch allows to change the way how the reactants, modifiers and products are presented in each reaction. If true, one table is created containing the identifiers of each reactant, modifier and product together with the respective name. If false (default), a subsection for each one of the three groups of participants is created giving all details of each participant.

Parameters:
arrangeReactionParticipantsInOneTable - True if the participants of the reactions should be arranged in small tables, false if a subsection should be created for the three groups.
